		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=6068"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=6068')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=46189&amp;TOPIC_ID=5686&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Fear+Portal+NPC&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         from personal experience, id be happy to tell you everything about this place</P><P>XP - anywhere from lv47 to lv54, my first try at her was 49 so dont sweat it too hard if you're lower.  she took me from 53 to 54 nice and easy</P><P>TRAVEL - all i can say about the spectre cave is..... get lucky, run your ass off, and fd /q once your on the other side</P><P>TACTICS - she is easy.  you can half-ass her.  go play chrono trigger or something for 6 minutes until she repops (i love that game!).  if you're rdy for a long stay looking for orange xp, try to get the max pet your spell will let you.  dont worry, theres plenty of skellys running around the portal for u to burn up bones ;).  always be sure to keep DMF, shielding arch/magi, resist disease up at all times.  be sure to kill her once she pops cuz if you let her get her pet up, its really annoying.  having these buffs on at all times will practically make you resist everything she throws at you.  she melees about 20% of the fight.  this is how i killed her</P><P>she pops, im sitting on the portal behind one of the fire pots, just out of skelly aggro range.<BR>-sick pet<BR>-get spammed with you resisting her spells ;)</P><P>-**SNARE HER**, IF U LET HER WALK INTO THE INVISIBLE WALL THERE IS A GOOD CHANCE SHE WILL AGGRO A SPEC</P><P>-nuke with a lifetap, insidious retrogression, incinerate/ignite bones, deflux.  any will do fine.  (i didnt use incinerate/ignite cuz my evoke sucks obviously!)<BR>-she has about 1400 hp, pure guess<BR>-2 nukes and your pet can finish her off</P><P>with the amount of energy you hafta use, lich is not needed.  you have enough mana left over and med time to rebuff EVERY buff after EVERY fight and still be back with 80%-FM when she repops</P><P></P><P>-have fun-</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
